# ─── Secrets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your values.

# AES-256-GCM key used to decrypt agent credentials from D1.
# Must match the key used by api-agent (agents.api_keys / channel_config encryption).
DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY="your_64_char_hex_key"

# WhatsApp credentials are no longer stored as env vars.
# They are read from the D1 `agents.api_keys` and `agents.channel_config` columns,
# which are encrypted at rest with DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY.
#
# To seed credentials for local dev:
#   1. Create .test-credentials.json (from .test-credentials.example.json)
#   2. Run: pnpm setup:dev && pnpm seed-credentials
#   3. This POSTs to the agent worker which encrypts and saves to D1.
#
# Required bindings (from wrangler.toml):
#   DB (D1 — platform-db)
#   AAF_KV (KV)
#   API_GATEWAY (service binding)
